        {
          "ruleId": "code_analyzer/D12",
          "ruleIndex": 2,
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Hardcoded model name: '\nPrometheus Metrics for SharkRouter.\n\nExposes key operational metrics for monitoring and alerting:\n- Request throughput by provider, tier, status\n- Latency histograms for LLM calls, KMS, cache, memory\n- Token usage by direction (input/output) and tier\n- Cost tracking in USD by tier and provider\n- Cache hit rates by scope\n- Active request gauge\n\nMetrics Naming Convention:\n- sharkrouter_* prefix for all metrics\n- Use labels for dimensions (provider, tier, status)\n- Histograms use _seconds suffix for latency\n- Counters use _total suffix\n\nUsage:\n    from observability.metrics import setup_metrics, record_request, record_latency\n\n    # At startup\n    setup_metrics(prometheus_port=9090)\n\n    # In request handlers\n    record_request(provider=\"openai\", tier=\"gold\", status=\"success\")\n    record_latency(\"llm_call\", 0.542, provider=\"openai\", model=\"gpt-4\")\n    record_tokens(input_tokens=150, output_tokens=300, tier=\"gold\")\n    record_cache_hit(scope=\"semantic\", hit=True)\n' — no routing/fallback"
          },
