          "ruleId": "code_analyzer/D12",
          "ruleIndex": 2,
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Hardcoded model name: '\nOpenTelemetry Distributed Tracing for SharkRouter.\n\nProvides:\n- TracerProvider with BatchSpanProcessor (low overhead)\n- PII scrubbing via PIIScrubbingSpanProcessor\n- Context propagation for trace correlation\n- X-Trace-Id header extraction for support tickets\n\nArchitecture:\n    HTTP Request\n         │\n         ▼\n    Extract Trace Context (W3C TraceContext or X-Trace-Id)\n         │\n         ▼\n    ┌────────────────────────────────────────┐\n    │           TracerProvider               │\n    │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐   │\n    │  │  PIIScrubbingSpanProcessor      │   │\n    │  │  └─ BatchSpanProcessor          │   │\n    │  │     └─ OTLPSpanExporter         │   │\n    │  └─────────────────────────────────┘   │\n    └────────────────────────────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n    Jaeger / OTLP Collector (PII-FREE!)\n\nUsage:\n    from observability.tracing import setup_tracing, get_tracer\n\n    # At startup\n    setup_tracing(\n        service_name=\"sharkrouter\",\n        otlp_endpoint=\"http://localhost:4317\",\n    )\n\n    # In request handlers\n    tracer = get_tracer()\n    with tracer.start_as_current_span(\"llm-call\") as span:\n        span.set_attribute(\"provider\", \"openai\")\n        span.set_attribute(\"model\", \"gpt-4\")\n        # Do NOT set prompts/responses - they'll be scrubbed anyway!\n        result = await call_llm()\n\n    # Get trace ID for response headers\n    trace_id = get_current_trace_id()\n    response.headers[\"X-Trace-Id\"] = trace_id\n' — no routing/fallback"
          },
