          "message": {
            "text": "Hardcoded model name: '\n    Async SharkRouter client — drop-in replacement for openai.AsyncOpenAI.\n\n    Usage:\n        client = SharkClient(\n            api_key=\"sk-shark-...\",\n            user_id=\"user-123\",\n        )\n\n        response = await client.chat.completions.create(\n            model=\"gpt-4o\",\n            messages=[{\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": \"Hello\"}],\n        )\n\n    Header behavior:\n        Every request automatically includes:\n        - X-Shark-User-ID: Persistent user identifier (set at init)\n        - X-Shark-Request-ID: Unique UUID4 per request (for audit correlation)\n        - X-Shark-Client-Version: SDK version string\n\n        These headers are injected via httpx event hooks and CANNOT be\n        overridden by extra_headers passed to individual API calls.\n    ' — no routing/fallback"
          },
          "locations": [
